//
// test/parse/recovery/expected-expr-after-binop.test — M2 Phase 5 /
// US3 (T052 companion of `specs/005-m2-parser/tasks.md`).
//
// **Specification anchors**:
//   - spec.md FR-027: locked-text diagnostic assertions on fail-case
//     fixtures.
//   - parser-recovery.contract.md §"Diagnostic output during
//     recovery" example 3: locked-text
//       expected expression after binary operator
//
// Single-error fixture: a binary operator (`+`) at the right edge of
// an expression with no following operand. The parser's Pratt loop
// MUST detect that `parseNudExpr()` cannot start a new primary at
// the post-`+` position and raise the contract's locked diagnostic.
//
// Recovery: per the contract, `parseExpr()` inherits the enclosing
// statement / decl's recovery set. In this fixture the enclosing
// scope is `parseSeqItem()` whose set is
// `{Semi, RBrace, if, for, while, goto, return}`. After raising,
// the parser skips to the seq-block's `}` and unwinds cleanly.
//
// **Locked-text drift caveat**: the exact wording Track L produces
// may differ. Flag any drift in the agent's final report.
//
// **FR-029 / Principle VIII RED state evidence**: against parent
// commit `39cc618`, `parseExpr()` returns nullptr on the missing
// operand; the diagnostic text the Phase-3+4 surface emits may not
// match the contract's golden form. CHECK likely fails at parent.

// RUN: not %nslc -emit=ast %s 2>&1 | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=ERR

module foo {
    proc p {
        seq {
            x := y +
        }
    }
}

// FR-027 locked-string assertion (contract's golden form).
// ERR: error: expected expression after binary operator
